modules.description: Computes mathematical operations including exponentials, logarithms, trigonometric functions, and hyperbolic functions, with specialized variants for improved accuracy near zero or for scaled inputs. Handles floating-point numbers and provides precise results for values close to critical points like zero or one. Used for numerical computations requiring high precision, such as scientific simulations or signal processing.

Computes elementary mathematical functions including exponential, logarithmic, trigonometric, and hyperbolic operations, with specialized variants for improved precision near zero or for scaled inputs. Operates on single-precision floating-point values and provides direct access to π-based trigonometric transformations. Used for numerical analysis, signal processing, and scientific computations requiring high accuracy in transcendental functions.

Computes mathematical functions with precision for values near zero, including exponential, logarithmic, trigonometric, and hyperbolic operations. Handles float inputs and provides results adjusted for numerical stability in edge cases. Used for scientific calculations requiring accurate transformations of floating-point numbers.

Provides elementary mathematical functions with correct rounding, including sin, cos, log, exp, and square root, implemented with precise control over rounding modes. Works with floating-point values of type float and supports custom rounding specifications. Used in applications requiring high-precision numerical computations, such as scientific simulations and financial calculations.

Provides accurate implementations of core mathematical functions including exponential, logarithmic, trigonometric, and hyperbolic operations, with specialized variants for improved precision near zero or specific ranges. Operates on 64-bit floating-point numbers and includes π-based variants for trigonometric calculations. Used in numerical computations requiring high accuracy, such as scientific simulations or financial modeling.
